race.comment: BLAZIN' FIRE (2) goes very well this course and distance starting five times for two wins and two minors. Below best last time at Maitland (23.07) in a Grade 5, finishing a 6 length sixth. With a clean break looks hard to beat. SIMPLICITY MAGIC (3) had a tricky draw and ran well to finish second, beaten a neck, (30.07) at Wentworth Park. Well-placed to take this out. FASCINATE VERN (1) is progressing well and looks close to another win after hitting the frame from Box 6 last run (29.86) at this track. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card last start despite being beaten. Expected to feature. HANK MCCOY (5) hit the frame latest (29.81) when second at this track in a Grade 5. Has already won out of this draw.
